data.title: Won't Disappoint
data.text:
This place has been around since the late 80's, therefore, they got to be doing something right.  Well guess what?  They are!

The pork ribs fall off the bone and are smokey good!

The beef brisket is tender, juicy and excellent.

You will not be disappointed.  Home made pecan pies too!

The people that run it are super nice too.

data.title: Blink and you would miss this Great BBQ Place
data.text:
This place is Located in a rough section of Daly City next to a former Gym, car repair shop and a great Mexican hole in the wall called Los Metates.  

The Great: their sauce! It was dark smokey spicy sweet and totally delicious. We loved it on the rib, which were some of the best we'd had in recent memory.

The Good: I can see that because we arrived pretty late in the day, that their chicken was a bit drier than it would have been. Could have been much juicer earlier in the day but, because of that sauce, still pretty good.

The OK: sweet potato pie. The pie filling was actually excellent, but the problem was that the crust was not done properly on the bottom, and was not as home-made as my wife (who is from the South) had hoped. An improved crust would have completely changed our impression of this pie.

But the BBQ is the authentic thing here and this had it in spades--saw them shoveling in the real wood in that black monster of a smoker.

OK a word about cleanliness: (avert your eyes of you care to not think about this) This is not one of the cleanest establishments I've been to. It's seen better days, and the stove and ovens could use a good going-over. But I've decided the quality of the BBQ is what I will focus on, and will take one star off for this area. If you are a "neat freak" for your BBQ you are now informed. 

Bottom-line: Will definitely go back.

data.title: Good southern food
data.text:
I've lived within walking distance from here for 3 months and just found out this place. I wish I would've found out about about it sooner! I am from the south and House of Catfish N Ribs rivals some of the best rib joints out there. I got the Ribs, Catfish and Brisket with a side of Potato Salad... all great. Yes, the HOT sauce is a little hot, but I'm from the south... I can take it! 
I am only in town temporarily, but if I lived here permanently, I would definitely come back!
*PS: Be sure to bring cash or be prepared to used their ATM*
